Package com.stardevllc.stardata.api.annotations

package com.stardevllc.stardata.api.annotations
  • Annotation Interfaces
    Class
    Description
    AutoIncrement
    This sets the field to be an auto-increment field
    Please see the Table class for more information on how to setup a table
    Codec
    This annotation allows you to tell the library a ObjectCodec for a field/column
    The MySQL type when using this feature is VARCHAR with a default length of 1000
    If you want to override this behavior, use the Type annotation.
    DBNotNull
    This annotation tells the library that the column cannot be null.
    FKOnDelete
    This annotation allows you to customize the behavior of foreign keys when an entry is deleted.
    FKOnUpdate
    This annotation allows you to customize the behavior of foreign keys when an entry is updated.
    ForeignKey
    This allows creating links between tables.
    ForeignKeyStorage
    This tells the library to use a field as storage.
    ID
    This annotation allows you to tell the library that this field is the id of the table.
    This will set the Primary Key flag to true as if you used the PrimaryKey annotation
    This will also set the auto_increment flag to true as if you used the AutoIncrement annotation and as long as the field is a supported number type
    Ignored
    When annotating a field with this annotation, the library will ignore that field within the table
    Name
    This annotation allows customization of the name of columns and tables in the database.
    Order
    This allows you to specify an order of the table columns.
    PrimaryKey
    This sets the field as the Primary Key
    Please see the Table class for more information on how to setup a table
    Type
    This annotation allows customization of the MySQL type.
    Unique
    Sets the column to be unique for that table
